sentence: Procter & Gamble ( PG ) is getting some attention from option buyers Thursday.
So far, 6,087 contracts of the Nov. 95call have changed hands, against open interest of 600 contracts.
Pricing suggests that today's volume was initiated from the buy side.
IK-> The technicals for PG ($88.72 down $0.73) are bullish with an upward trend.
Look at the Dec. 80/82.50 bull-put spread for a 23-cent credit.
That's a 10.1% return and the stock has to fall by 7.0% to cause a problem.
